        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 3:51PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Halls Mills, or over Mc Grady, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Traphill...
Mc Grady...
Hays...
Abshers...
Halls Mills...
Doughton Park...
and Dockery.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
